item.title: Residents urged to leave ‘high-risk’ homes
item.description: Residents will be asked to leave 18 oceanfront homes deemed as being at “high-risk” of a coastal erosion crisis on the NSW central coast.

item.title: JobKeeper wind-back to target ‘overpaid’
item.description: The federal opposition says it “makes sense” to wind back JobKeeper in instances where people were making more money than usual under the $70 billion scheme.

item.title: Life or death moment for NSW
item.description: NSW’s Transport Minister says the state is at a “critical juncture” in its fight against coronavirus, with thousands of schoolchildren expected back on the public transport network next week.

item.title: 18 new cases confirmed in NSW
item.description: Eighteen new cases of COVID-19 have been confirmed in NSW, bringing the state’s total to 3379 since the pandemic began.

item.title: Metro works reveal iconic new view
item.description: Sydney Tower can be seen from almost every point of the Harbour City – now it can even be spotted from underground.

item.title: Push for free childcare for all
item.description: The Australian Council of Trade Unions is calling for free, universal childcare to be introduced in Australia as part of a national jobs plan to reconstruct the economy after the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Where Melbourne’s cases are spreading
item.description: More than 80 per cent of Victoria’s coronavirus cases since mid-May were spread at workplaces, Premier Daniel Andrews said on Sunday as he announced 363 new cases and three deaths for the state.

item.title: Teen dies in northern beaches car crash
item.description: A teenager is dead after a horrific car crash in a semirural street of Sydney’s northern beaches overnight.

item.title: Premier’s dig at ‘Karen from Brighton’
item.description: Victorian Premier Daniel Andrews has made a subtle dig at a Melbourne woman who shot to social media fame after telling a reporter she was sick of walking the same streets and declaring “I’ve done all of Brighton”.

item.title: Raucous party ‘put whole state at risk’
item.description: A NSW MP says a raucous house party in Sydney’s northwest, which has led to more than $60,ooo in fines for breaching coronavirus rules, has “put the whole state at risk”.
